<br>
As it stands, to get bash up and going will require 3 hot key slots to use it somewhat effectively.  One for the secondary hand slot.  Another for the inventory slot where the shield is and yet another for the bash key itself.  This doesn't even take into consideration that I lose a slot that could be holding a bag in inventory only so I can get to a shield faster that's going to be used maybe 1% of the time.<br>
<br>
&quot;Just be glad you're not a bard, with their hotkey boxes. Spells, plus swap spots, plus any special hotkeys they decide they need.&quot;<br>
<br>
This is why I play classes like a monk or a warrior.  I considered a bard but chose against it entirely based on all the swapping required.  It's also part of the reason why there are so few bards and bard equipment is dirt cheap.  If I wanted to do all this swapping and pad switching I would have chosen a bard in the first place. <br>
<br>
Yes, I like being the best I can be in any of my chosen classes which is why I'm even exploring this option, however, I also want to still be the best monk I can be without having to spend 30 minutes redefining linked keys every time I bring him up.<br>
<br>
I'll figure out something to make it work but what you suggest won't be happening anytime soon.  Thanks though ;&gt;<br>
<br>
<br>
Strike<br>
